## ðŸ“Š **Defense-in-Depth Testing Pyramid**

### Coverage Targets

**Business Requirement (BR) Coverage** - OVERLAPPING:
- **Unit**: 70%+ of ALL BRs (maximum coverage foundation)
- **Integration**: >50% of ALL BRs (critical interactions)
- **E2E**: <10% BR coverage (essential user journeys)

**Code Coverage** - CUMULATIVE (~100% combined):
- **Unit**: 70%+ code coverage (algorithms, edge cases, error handling)
- **Integration**: 50% code coverage (cross-component flows, CRD operations)
- **E2E**: 50% code coverage (full stack, deployment wiring, real infrastructure)

**Key Insight**: With 70%/50%/50% code coverage targets, **50%+ of codebase is tested in ALL 3 tiers** - bugs must slip through multiple defense layers to reach production.

**See**: [Complete Testing Strategy](mdc:docs/testing/PYRAMID_TEST_MIGRATION_GUIDE.md)

